<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The expression (void *) tiny_body casts away the const-qualification of tiny_body (which is a static string / const char[] or const char *). That produces a void * that points to a non-const type even though the data is immutable. This discarding of const violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13 (pointers should point to const-qualified types whenever possible). The correct fix is to preserve const (e.g. use an API accepting const void * or use the static response helper that takes a const buffer) rather than casting away const.
</scenario>
